        "title": "The challenge of back orders and how to address them:",
        "style": null,
        "contentBefore": "",
        "items": [
            {
                "text": "<p>Backorders are a good thing. To define backorder, just think of having more orders than you have products in stock &ndash; this is what it ultimately comes down to when we ask a question of &quot;what does backordered mean?&quot; It can be a dream come true for any retail business, however, it can become a big challenge if you don&#39;t know how to deal with it.&nbsp;</p>\n"
            },
            {
                "text": "<p>Here is a common situation: You get a sales order, but there are one or two items in it that are out of stock. Not a big deal, right? You simply make a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://virtocommerce.com/glossary/purchase-order-management-software\">purchase order</a>&nbsp;for the missing items and let your customer know when the backordered items are going to be available.&nbsp;</p>\n"
            }
        ],
        "noTop": null,
        "noBottom": true,
        "noPad": null
    },
    {
        "id": 4,
        "type": "text",
        "name": null,
        "title": null,
        "style": null,
        "decorator": null,
        "content": "<p>Now, imagine you&#39;re managing hundreds of different orders per day, many having back ordered items. Spread across several sales orders you get a multitude of products backordered meaning you need to consolidate all the out of stock products from multiple sales orders into a purchase order. If the items that fall under the &quot;out of stock&quot; definition must be purchased from different suppliers &ndash; now what does backorder mean for your business?</p>\n",
        "url": null,
        "noTop": true,
        "noBottom": true,
        "noPad": null
    },
    {
        "id": 5,
        "type": "list-with-images",
        "name": null,
        "title": "Dealing with Backorders",
        "intro": "<p>The logistics of dealing with backorders can be extremely challenging for retailers. In order to fulfill back orders efficiently a retail business needs to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Make sure all the sale orders with items on backorder are accurately recorded</li>\n\t<li>Place a purchase order for these items with the supplier</li>\n\t<li>Upon re-stocking, go through all the recorded sales orders to match these to the correct purchase order</li>\n</ul>\n",
        "style": null,
        "colStyle": null,
        "items": [],
        "noTop": null,
        "noBottom": true,
        "noPad": null
    },
    {
        "id": 6,
        "type": "two-columns-text",
        "name": null,
        "title": "Best customer service practices when dealing with backorders:",
        "style": null,
        "contentBefore": null,
        "items": [
            {
                "text": "<p>Once you reach a point of having too many backorders to effectively fulfill them, using spreadsheets won&#39;t be enough anymore. At this stage, you might want to consider getting a proper&nbsp;<a href=\"https://virtocommerce.com/glossary/what-is-inventory-management\">inventory management</a>&nbsp;system that will automatically consolidate and track back orders for you.</p>\n"
            },
            {
                "text": "<p>Offering to get products backordered means increased sales and more customers. However, it is important to remember what backorder is - you are essentially asking your customers to pay for a product in advance. Naturally, they&#39;ll be worried and expecting regular updates, so timely communication is essential.</p>\n"
            }
        ],
        "noTop": null,
        "noBottom": true,
        "noPad": null
    },
    {
        "id": 7,
        "type": "text",
        "name": null,
        "title": null,
        "style": null,
        "decorator": null,
        "content": "<p>Customers waiting for their backordered products will expect&nbsp;to receive shipping notifications on the shipping date they&#39;ve been provided. So always keeping your customers in the loop in case of any delays or changes will help avoid complaints and help maintain your company&#39;s reputation. Send out regular emails, update buyers, provide estimated times of arrival, and you&#39;ll keep your happy customers loyal. Also key: a good inventory tracking system will help you can keep track of backorders and make sure your customers aren&#39;t left waiting for too long.</p>\n",
